    "extras": [
      "Use December to March or July to August for the cleanest weather mix across Bogotá, the Coffee Region, and the Caribbean coast.",
      "Carry small cash for Cocora jeeps, Minca moto-taxis, market snacks, and some island boat add-ons even though cities are mostly card-friendly.",
      "Book San Andrés flights early and remember the separate OCCRE tourist card fee before you board.",
      "Tayrona trail conditions and boat departures can change quickly after rain, so keep at least one flexible buffer if the coast is a priority.",
      "If you are short on time, keep Bogotá, Medellín, Cartagena, and either Salento or Santa Marta as the core route, then add San Andrés last.",
      "Domestic fares look cheap until baggage is added, so compare Avianca and LATAM with carry-on rules included instead of headline fare alone."
